The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 2: The government is learnt to have approached the Company Law Board to recall its six directors from the board of IT firm Mahindra Satyam (earlier Satyam Computer). The board of Mahindra Satyam will meet on July 10 to discuss the second round of preferential share allotment to raise Tech Mahindras stake in the firm to about 42.7 per cent.                            
	 New Delhi, July 2: Inflation fell to (-)1.3 per cent for the week ended June 20, staying in the negative for the third week in a row, because of a high base effect even as prices of food items such as fruits and vegetables rose compared with the same week last year. The rate of price rise was (-)1.14 per cent in the previous week.                             
	 New Delhi, July 2: The government today approved the re-introduction of the new Companies Bill, which would replace the old law enacted in 1956. The bill lapsed without any changes following the dissolution of the earlier Lok Sabha .                            
	 Mumbai, July 2: The government may convert the US and Europe into focused markets with the countrys exports declining for the eighth month in a row in May, R.S. Gujral, director-general of foreign trade, said.                             
	 New Delhi, July 2: The countrys software sector is likely to miss the target of touching $60 billion in exports by fiscal 2010 because of the slowdown in key markets such as the US and Europe, IT industry body Nasscom said.                            
	 New Delhi, July 2: The government today said Reliance Industries would have to pay a royalty on natural gas it was producing from the KG basin fields according to the production sharing contract signed with it.                            
	 Calcutta, July 2: Indian Oil Corporation has released a vision statement for the organisation on the eve of the company completing 50 years. It is celebrating its golden jubilee from July to September.                                                                                                                           
